1. **Add the Image for the Delete Button**: Use an image that represents a delete action, such as a trash can icon. You can place this image inside your HTML where you want the delete button to appear.

2. **Wrap the Image in a Button or Link**: To make the image interactive, wrap it in a `<button>` or an `<a>` tag. This will allow you to attach an event listener to it.

3. **Add JavaScript for the Delete Action**: Use JavaScript to define what should happen when the delete button is clicked. This could involve removing an element from the DOM or performing another action.

Here's an example of how you can implement a delete button using an image:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<style>
body, html {
  height: 100%;
  margin: 0;
}

.bg {
  background-image: url("img/bg.png");
  height: 100%;
  background-position: center;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: cover;
}

.rounded-corners {
  border-radius: 25px;
  border: 2px solid #030126;
  padding: 20px;
  width: 500px;
  height: 550px;
  background-color: #030126;
  margin: auto;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.text {
  color: white;
  font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
  margin-left: 10px;
}

img {
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  cursor: pointer; /* Change cursor to pointer to indicate it's clickable */
}

</style>
</head>
<body class="bg">
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<div class="rounded-corners">
  <img src="img/profile.png" alt="profile">
  <p id="welcomeMessage" class="text">Welcome!</p>
  <!-- Delete button -->
  <button id="deleteButton" style="background: none; border: none; padding: 0;">
    <img src="img/delete.png" alt="Delete" title="Delete">
  </button>
</div>
</body>
<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
    var name = localStorage.getItem("user");
    if (name) {
      document.getElementById("welcomeMessage").innerText += " " + name;
    }

    // Add event listener for delete button
    document.getElementById("deleteButton").addEventListener("click", function() {
      // Example delete action: remove the welcome message
      document.getElementById("welcomeMessage").remove();
    });
  });
</script>

</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **Image as Button**: The delete button is created using an image (`img/delete.png`) wrapped inside a `<button>` element. The button has no background or border to make the image appear as the button itself.
- **JavaScript Event Listener**: An event listener is added to the button to perform a delete action when clicked. In this example, it removes the welcome message, but you can customize this action as needed.

Make sure to replace `"img/delete.png"` with the path to your delete icon image."}],"context":{"currentFile":{"path":"home.html","fsPath":"/Users/Sakshi/PycharmProjects/fintrack/home.html","sources":["opened_tab"],"content":"<!DOCTYPE html>
