 ","refToolCallId":"toolu_014uipgC19oamupCWTWEv1KW"},{"type":"text","text":"I've fixed the "Show More" functionality in your application. Here's what was wrong and how I fixed it:

### The Problem
The issue was in how the full note text was being passed to the `toggleNoteVisibility` function. The code was trying to use backticks to escape the notes within an inline event handler, which can lead to problems when notes contain special characters.

### The Solution
I've made these changes:
1. Removed the inline `onclick` attribute from the "Show More" button
2. Added the button without any event handling in the HTML template
3. Added a proper event listener to each button after the element is created
4. This approach passes the original notes directly to the function without any string escaping issues

Now the "Show More" button should work correctly for both income and expense entries, regardless of what special characters might be in the notes."},{"type":"codePatch","diffs":[{"path":"home.html","patch":"@@ -5595,193 +5595,8 @@

