```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<style>
/* Existing styles... */

.list-container {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 20px;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  width: 90%;
  background-color: #fff;
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 10px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.list-item {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding: 5px 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;
}

.list-item:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
}

.income {
  color: green;
}

.expense {
  color: red;
}
</style>
</head>
<body class="bg">
<!-- Existing content... -->

<div class="rounded-corners" id="contentDiv">
  <!-- Existing elements... -->

  <!-- New list section -->
  <div class="list-container">
    <div class="list-item">
      <span class="text">Salary</span>
      <span class="text income">$5000</span>
    </div>
    <div class="list-item">
      <span class="text">Rent</span>
      <span class="text expense">-$1500</span>
    </div>
    <!-- Add more items as needed -->
  </div>
</div>

<script>
// Existing scripts...
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **CSS**: Added styles for `.list-container` and `.list-item` to style the list of income and expenses. The `.income` and `.expense` classes are used to differentiate between income (green) and expense (red).
- **HTML**: Added a new `div` with the class `list-container` inside the `rounded-corners` div. This contains multiple `div` elements with the class `list-item` to represent each income or expense entry.

