Here's a quick review of the relevant parts of your code:

### HTML
```html
<div class="tab">
  <button class="tablinks" onclick="openTab(event, 'Income')" id="defaultOpen">Income</button>
  <button class="tablinks" onclick="openTab(event, 'Expense')">Expense</button>
</div>
```

### JavaScript
```javascript
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
  // Other initialization code...

  document.getElementById("defaultOpen").click(); // This line opens the Income tab by default
});
```

### Explanation
- **HTML**: The `id="defaultOpen"` is assigned to the Income tab button.
- **JavaScript**: The `document.getElementById("defaultOpen").click();` line simulates a click on the Income tab button when the page loads, ensuring it is the default open tab.

