1. **Ensure the Note Text is Displayed as a Block Element**: By default, `<span>` elements are inline, which might cause the text to extend horizontally. You can change this by setting the display property to `block` or `inline-block`.

2. **Modify the JavaScript Function**: Ensure that the JavaScript function correctly toggles the note text and updates the button text.

Here's how you can implement these changes:

### HTML & CSS Changes

Ensure your CSS for the note text allows it to expand vertically:

```css
.note-text {
  display: inline-block; /* Change to block or inline-block */
  max-width: 100%; /* Ensure it doesn't overflow horizontally */
  word-wrap: break-word; /* Ensure long words break to the next line */
}
```

### JavaScript Changes

Ensure the `toggleNoteVisibility` function correctly toggles the note text:

```javascript
function toggleNoteVisibility(button, fullNote) {
  const noteSpan = button.previousElementSibling; // Get the span element containing the note
  const maxNoteLength = 20;

  if (noteSpan.textContent.includes('...')) {
    // Currently truncated, show full note
    noteSpan.textContent = fullNote;
    button.innerText = "Show Less";
  } else {
    // Currently showing full note, truncate it
    noteSpan.textContent = fullNote.substring(0, maxNoteLength) + '...';
    button.innerText = "Show More";
  }
}
```

### Explanation

- **CSS**: By setting the `.note-text` class to `inline-block`, you allow the text to wrap and extend downwards naturally. The `word-wrap: break-word;` ensures that long words do not overflow the container.

- **JavaScript**: The `toggleNoteVisibility` function checks if the note is currently truncated (contains '...'). If it is, it expands to show the full note and changes the button text to "Show Less". If the full note is displayed, it truncates the note and changes the button text back to "Show More".

These changes should ensure that when "Show More" is pressed, the full note is displayed extending downwards."}],"context":{"currentFile":{"path":"home.html","fsPath":"/Users/Sakshi/PycharmProjects/fintrack/home.html","sources":["opened_tab"],"content":"<!DOCTYPE html>
