### CSS Adjustments

1. **Ensure Text Wrapping**: Use `word-wrap: break-word;` to ensure long words break to the next line.
2. **Set Display to Block**: Ensure the note text is displayed as a block element.

Here's the updated CSS:

```css
.note-text {
  display: block; /* Ensure the text is displayed as a block */
  word-wrap: break-word; /* Break long words to the next line */
  max-width: 100%; /* Ensure it doesn't overflow horizontally */
}

td {
  vertical-align: top; /* Align text to the top of the cell */
}
```

### HTML and JavaScript Adjustments

Ensure your JavaScript function for toggling notes is correctly implemented:

```javascript
function toggleNoteVisibility(button, fullNote) {
  const noteSpan = button.previousElementSibling; // Get the span element containing the note
  const maxNoteLength = 20;

  if (noteSpan.textContent.includes('...')) {
    // Currently truncated, show full note
    noteSpan.textContent = fullNote;
    button.innerText = "Show Less";
  } else {
    // Currently showing full note, truncate it
    noteSpan.textContent = fullNote.substring(0, maxNoteLength) + '...';
    button.innerText = "Show More";
  }
}
```

### Explanation

- **CSS**: The `.note-text` class is set to `display: block;` to ensure the text extends downwards. The `word-wrap: break-word;` ensures that long words do not cause horizontal scrolling.
- **JavaScript**: The `toggleNoteVisibility` function toggles between showing the full note and a truncated version, updating the button text accordingly.

