### CSS Changes

Add the following CSS to adjust the layout:

```css
.rounded-corners-balance .details {
  text-align: center; /* Center the balance */
}

.detail {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between; /* Align income to the left and expense to the right */
  margin-top: 20px; /* Add some space between balance and income/expense */
}

.income, .expense {
  width: 45%; /* Ensure both income and expense take equal space */
}
```

### Explanation

- **Remove Summary Text**: By removing the `<h1>` tag, the "Summary" text will no longer appear.
- **Center the Balance**: The `text-align: center;` property in `.rounded-corners-balance .details` centers the balance text.
- **Align Income and Expense**: The `display: flex;` and `justify-content: space-between;` properties in `.detail` ensure that the income and expense are on the same line, with income on the left and expense on the right.

